			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">&quot;Envelope decay&quot; is an automatic fade-out (or automatic volume change).<br /><br />It operates on the same 'period' concept... you provide a period P and after P+1 clocks, the output volume will change.<br /><br />The key thing to note, though, is that the clocks do not come from the APU clock, but rather from the Frame Sequencer, which is almost like an entirely separate subunit within the APU.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">APU clock -&gt; Channel Timer -&gt; Duty Cycle -&gt; Channel Output<br /><br />APU clock -&gt; Frame Sequencer -&gt; Envelope Period -&gt; Volume change<br /></div><br /><br />The sweep unit operates similarly, but changes the pitch/timer, rather than the volume:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">APU clock -&gt; Frame Sequencer -&gt; Sweep Period -&gt; Channel Timer change<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
