					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">@oRBIT2002<br /><br />You see. The NTSC refresh rate is 60FPS (or very near that). So, if a unit runs at 240hz, it's updated 4 times per frame. Well, you got it - 120hz means 2 times per frame, and so on. The frequency value is merely the number of CPU cycles to wait.</div>

